!! What Will Heaven Be Like?
!!! New (v.1)
The word new appears 4 times, twice in verse 1. Once in verse 2. Once in verse 5. Newness is clearly a theme. It is the more specific one. The more common word for new.

The Word used here is a more specific one. Here the word new is also a qualitative sense. It is also something that is brand new, fresh, radically different.

!!!! New Skye
The new heaven. It is speaking not about the abode of God but rather the sky. "new Heaven and a new earth" usually means by sky and Earth Genesis 1.

!!!! No More Sea
There are no seas and no oceans. This probably symbolized the end of the separation of people groups. Oceans divide people groups. We are one big unified family of God.

!!!! The Curse is Reversed (cf v4)
The new Earth and heaven is a return to Eden.

<<<
He will wipe away every tear from their eyes, and death shall be no more, neither shall there be mourning, nor crying, nor pain anymore, for the former things have passed away.
<<<
Revelations 21:4

The Bible comes full circle. It ends how it begins. God's perfect creation apart from the curse. No more sea to divide up the people groups.

!!!! An Earth
The new Earth is an Earth, it is not just Spiritual but an actual place. 1 Corinthians 15 says we have a resurrected body so we need places on a physical Earth.

Our experience on the eternal heaven is on a physical body and on a physical Earth. Think less floating around and more about your feet touching down on Earth. Living a life very much like you do now. Think less being in a surreal dream like state and think more about being fully conscious and fully aware. In heaven we will be in so many activities on Earth.

* Revelations 22:2
** There is fruit, you can touch the trunk of the tree with your physical hands

